INTRODUCTION¶

I will be wrangling and analyzing @weratedogs tweets to demonstrate data wrangling proficiency and develop interesting and trustworthy analysis and visualizations.

I will gather data with three different methods.

I will assess my data for quality and tidiness both visually and programmatically.

I will clean up my data based on observed quality and tidyness issues assessed.

I will carry out an exploratory data anlysis to get insights from the data.

I will share my analysis in form of visuals to resonate better with audience with lame code understanding

I will derive and share some conclusions from the insights derived from the data

I will share some limitations to my analysis based on the resources available if any.

I will provide any recommendations for we rate dogs if necessary.

QUESTIONS¶

In this section of this report, I will state the problem question, describe the questions that I plan on exploring over the course of this report.

The Problem Question¶

Question - How does we rate dogs give rating and how do audience engage the tweets based on dog breeds and dog stage?

My Explorative Questions¶

I will be exploring the tweets using these two variables( Breeds and Dog stage).

Breed

Which dog breeds have the highest average rating?

Which dog breeds have the highest retweet_counts?

Which dog breeds have the highest favorite_count?

Which dog breeds have the highest engagements?

Dog Stage

Which dog stage has the highest average rating?

Which dog stage has the highest retweet_counts?

Which dog stage has the highest engagements?

2) DATA ASSESSMENT¶

I will be assessing my data both visually and programmatically for quality and tidyness.¶

Quality

Data that has issues with data content.

  • Missing data
  • Duplicate data
  • Invalid data
  • Inaccurate data.

Tidyness

Data that has issues with its structure, like rows, columns and table.

  • Each Variable forms a column
  • Each Obserevation forms a row
  • Each type of observational unit forms a table

Data Assesssment Dimensions

  • COMPLETENESS - Missing data.

  • VALIDITY - Conformation of data to pre-established schema.

  • ACCURACY - Appropriateness of data even though it conforms to schema.

  • CONSISITENCY - Representation of data to a standard format.

Quality issues¶

  1. There are some incorrect dog names, some names are represented by 'a'. - Accuracy

  2. The majority of values in the retweet and replies columns are null- Completeness

  3. There are some dogs with name shown as 'None'. - Accuracy

  4. There are a lot of dogs neither identified as Doggo, puppo, pupper nor floofer. - Completeness

Tidiness issues¶

  1. All columns apart from text, rating_numerator, rating_denominator, name, doggo, floofer, pupper, puppo are not needed for our analysis.

  2. The dog classification should just be one column( Dogo, puppo, pupper or floofer.)

  3. All rows with retweets and replies are not needed as part of our analysis.

All Issues Observed¶

Quality¶

twitter_archive

  1. There are some denominators that are greater than 10.- Validity

  2. There are some numerators are far greater than 10. - Validity

  3. The majority of values in the retweets columns are null- Completeness

  4. The majority of values in the reply columns are null- Completeness

  5. There are some tweets assigned to mutiple dog stages. - Quality

  6. There are some dogs with name shown as 'a' or 'an'. - Accuracy

  7. The tweet id is in integer form and not string - validity

df_predict

  1. Some tweets have all the image predictions false for a breed. - Completeness

  2. The tweet ID column was sorted in ascending order which is not consisitent with the twitter archive table.- Consistency

  3. The tweet id is in integer form and not string. - validity

  4. The real dog breed should be extracted from the three predictions. - Completeness

df_engage

  1. There were some rows in the favorite_count column that had 0 count and that is likely impossible for a post with so much retweet_count. - Accuracy

  2. The tweet id is in string form and not integer. - validity

Tidyness¶

twitter_archive

  1. All rows with retweets and replies are not needed as part of our analysis.

  2. All columns apart from text, rating_numerator, rating_denominator, name, doggo, floofer, pupper, puppo are not needed for our analysis.

  3. The dog classification should just be one column( doggo, puppo, pupper or floofer.)

  4. This row should be joined with image predictions and engagement to give just one table.

df_predict

  1. Only tweeet_id and the predicted_breed are necessary in this table.

  2. This table should be joined with twitter_archive and engagements to give one table.

df_engage

  1. All the rows with reply, retweets and quoted tweets are not necessary for analysis.

  2. Apart from the tweet id, favorite_count and the retweet count column, all other columns are redundant and should be removed.

  3. A column that cumulates the total engagements should be in the table

  4. The table should be joined to the twitter archive and the image predictions to make just one table.

1) Visualization by DOG BREED¶

A) COMMON BREEDS¶

5 Most common breeds¶

In [139]:
plt.figure(figsize = (12,5)) 
sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid')
df_breed = df.groupby('predicted_breed', as_index=False)[['tweet_id']].count().sort_values('tweet_id', ascending=False).head(5)
breed_analysis =sns.barplot(
    x = "predicted_breed",
    y= "tweet_id",
    data = df_breed,
    estimator = sum,
    palette= sns.color_palette("Set2"),
    ci = None,

)
plt.title('Most Common Predicted breeds',  fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel('Dog breed', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold');
plt.savefig('Most_common_breeds.png')

CONCLUSION ( Insights Summary )¶

Dog Breed¶

Golden retriever and labrador retriever are the most rated breeds.

Clumber breed is the rated breed of dog with the highest average rating.

Japanese Spaniel is the rated breed of dog with the lowest average raing.

Saluki and Bedlington terrier are the rated breeds with the highest average engagements.

Brabancon griffon is the rated breed of dog with the lowest average engagement.

Dog Stage¶

Pupper is the most assigned dog stage.

Puppo dogs are the dogs with the highest average rating.

Puppo and doggo are the most loved dog stages by the audience.

LIMITATIONS¶

A lot of dogs were not classified into stages.

We can't guarantee that the breed predictions are all correct.

The ratings were exceptionally much for some breeds which will affect the average ratings.
